+	BUG_ON(host->bus_refs);

WARNING:AVOID_BUG: Avoid crashing the kernel - try using WARN_ON & recovery code rather than BUG() or BUG_ON()
#194: FILE: drivers/mmc/core/core.c:49:
+	BUG_ON(!host->bus_dead);

CHECK:UNNECESSARY_PARENTHESES: Unnecessary parentheses around 'host->bus_refs == 0'
#214: FILE: drivers/mmc/core/core.c:69:
+	if ((host->bus_refs == 0) && host->bus_ops)

Parentheses are not required in the following cases:

  1. Function pointer uses::

      (foo->bar)();

    could be::

      foo->bar();

  2. Comparisons in if::

      if ((foo->bar) && (foo->baz))
      if ((foo == bar))

    could be::

      if (foo->bar && foo->baz)
      if (foo == bar)

  3. addressof/dereference single Lvalues::

      &(foo->bar)
      *(foo->bar)

    could be::

      &foo->bar
      *foo->bar

